revision.text:
{{Infobox summit | summit_name = Rome summit | image = NATO expansion.png | caption = Map of NATO members | country = Italy | venues = [[Pratica di Mare Air Force Base]] | dates = May 28, 2002 }}
The '''2002 Rome summit''' was an exceptional (and thus unnumbered) [[NATO summit]] of NATO and Russia at the level of Heads of State and Government. [[NATO]] Allies and the [[Russia|Russian Federation]] created the [[NATO–Russia relations|NATO–Russia Council]], which replaced the NATO–Russia Permanent Joint Council. The summit was held in the [[Pratica di Mare Air Base]] outside [[Rome]] because of outstanding security requirements soon after the [[september 11 attacks|9/11]] attacks.
