{{Infobox wildfire | title =Bogart Fire | image =Bogart Fire 30-8-2016.jpg | caption = Smoke billows from the Bogart fire as seen from Oak Glen Road | cost = | injuries = | fatalities = | reference =<ref name="cdf">{{cite web|title=Bogart Fire|url=http://www.rvcfire.org/_Layouts/Incident%20Information/IncidentInfoDetail.aspx?2843|website=[[CALFIRE]]|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref> <!-- ONLY FOR INDIVIDUAL FIRES --> | date = {{Start date|2016|8|30}} ~ {{End date|2016|9|02}} | location =[[Cherry Valley, California|Cherry Valley]], [[Riverside County]], [[California]] | coordinates = {{coord|33.976676|-116.954740|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = USA California Southern | pushpin_map_caption = Location of fire in Southern California | area = {{Convert| 1,470 |acre|km2|0}} | buildings = | cause =Human related | landuse = | perps = | motive = }}
The '''Bogart Fire''' was a [[wildfire]] in the Bogart Park area of [[Cherry Valley, California|Cherry Valley]] In [[Riverside, California|Riverside County, California]].<ref name="cdf" /> The fire broke out near Winesap Avenue and International Park Road just southwest of Bogart Park on August 30, 2016. By August 31, the fire was estimated at 1,300 acres.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pe.com/articles/fire-811954-park-bogart.html|title=1,250-acre Bogart fire caused by humans, officials say (UPDATE 13)|date=31 August 2016|work=pe.com|agency=[[The Press Enterprise]]|last1=Brooks|first1=Richard|last2=Tadayon|first2=Ali|accessdate=31 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fire.ca.gov/current_incidents/incidentdetails/Index/1416|title=Bogart Fire|date=31 August 2016|accessdate=31 August 2016}}</ref>
== Events == The fire was first reported at 12:25 pm on August 30 at Bogart Park near Winesap Avenue and International Park Road. The fire soon forced the evacuation of 700 residents within the Highland Spring Village mobile home park and of residents in the Banning Bench area near [[Banning, California|Banning]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.scpr.org/news/2016/08/30/64142/fast-moving-riverside-county-fire-burns-120-acres/|title=Fast-moving Riverside County fire leads to mandatory evacuations|date=30 August 2016|work=scpr.org|agency=[[KPCC]]|first1=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> 4 firefighters sustained minor injuries and one outbuilding was destroyed by the wildfire.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ktla.com/2016/08/30/firefighters-battling-400-acre-brush-fire-in-beaumont-area-rv-park-threatened/|title=1,000-Acre Bogart Fire Determined to Be Human-Caused; All Evacuations Lifted|date=30 August 2016|work=ktla.com|agency=[[KTLA 5]]|last1=Gutierrez-Jaime|first1=Nisha|last2=Von Quednow|first2=Cindy|last3=Yost|first3=Chip|last4=Montoya|first4=Casey|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> In addition, more than 500 firefighters battled the fire.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pe.com/articles/fire-812296-bogart-named.html|title=Bogart fire is nearly surrounded at 95 percent containment|date=30 August 2016|work=pe.com|agency=[[The Press Enterprise]]|last1=Millerbernd|first1=Anne|accessdate=2 September 2016}}</ref>
By September 2, the fire was 100% contained at 1,470 acres in size.<ref name="cdf">{{cite web|title=Bogart Fire|url=http://www.rvcfire.org/_Layouts/Incident%20Information/IncidentInfoDetail.aspx?2843|website=[[CALFIRE]]|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref>
== Cause == According to [[CALFIRE]], the fire is believed to be caused by “juvenile activity” near Bogart Park in Beaumont.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-southern-california-fires-20160831-snap-story.html|title=Hot and breezy conditions fan fires burning in Riverside, Orange counties|date=31 August 2016|work=latimes.com|agency=[[Los Angeles Times]]|last1=Serna|first1=Joseph|accessdate=31 August 2016}}</ref>
